# Plan: Extract Service Layer from Express Route Handlers

## Context

`src/routes/products.ts` and `src/routes/orders.ts` currently mix HTTP concerns (parsing
requests, sending responses) with business logic (filtering, validation, stock management,
order creation, status transitions). This makes the logic hard to unit-test in isolation
and couples business rules to the HTTP layer. The refactor extracts all business logic into
dedicated service files, leaving route handlers as thin HTTP adapters.

---

## Files to Create

### `src/services/service-error.ts` (new)
A shared typed error class used by both services to signal failures to the route layer.

```typescript
export class ServiceError extends Error {
  constructor(message: string, public readonly status: number) {
    super(message);
    this.name = "ServiceError";
  }
}
```

---

### `src/services/product-service.ts` (new)
All product business logic extracted from `src/routes/products.ts`.

**Exported types:**
- `ListProductsFilter` — `{ category?: string; minPrice?: number; maxPrice?: number }`
- `ProductListResult` — `{ products: Product[]; summary: { count, totalInventoryValue, averagePrice } }`
- `ProductDetail extends Product` — adds `isLowStock: boolean; inventoryValue: number`

**Exported functions:**
- `listProducts(filter: ListProductsFilter): ProductListResult` — filters products array, computes summary stats; never throws
- `getProductById(id: number): ProductDetail` — finds product or throws `ServiceError("Product not found", 404)`; computes `isLowStock` and `inventoryValue` via private `toProductDetail()` helper
- `adjustStock(id: number, adjustment: number): ProductDetail` — finds product (or 404), checks `newStock < 0` (or 400), mutates `product.stock`, returns `toProductDetail(product)`

**Imports:** `products` from `../data.js`, `Product` type from `../types.js`, `ServiceError` from `./service-error.js`

---

### `src/services/order-service.ts` (new)
All order business logic extracted from `src/routes/orders.ts`.

**Exported types:**
- `ListOrdersFilter` — `{ userId?: number; status?: string }`
- `OrderListResult` — `{ orders: Order[]; summary: { count, totalRevenue } }`
- `EnrichedOrderItem extends OrderItem` — adds `productName: string`
- `EnrichedOrder extends Omit<Order, "items">` — replaces `items` with `EnrichedOrderItem[]`

**Exported functions:**
- `listOrders(filter: ListOrdersFilter): OrderListResult` — filters by `userId` and/or `status`, computes `totalRevenue`; never throws
- `getOrderById(id: number): EnrichedOrder` — finds order (or 404), enriches each item with `productName` via `product?.name ?? "Unknown"`
- `createOrder(input: CreateOrderInput): Order` — validates `userId`/`items` presence (400), non-empty items (400), then per-item: product exists (400), quantity > 0 (400), sufficient stock (400); deducts stock, builds and pushes the order, returns it
- `updateOrderStatus(id: number, status: string): Order` — finds order (or 404), validates against `VALID_STATUSES` constant (400), validates `STATUS_TRANSITIONS[order.status]` allows target (400), mutates and returns order

**Module-level constants:**
```typescript
const VALID_STATUSES = ["pending", "confirmed", "shipped", "delivered"] as const;
const STATUS_TRANSITIONS: Record<string, string[]> = {
  pending: ["confirmed"], confirmed: ["shipped"], shipped: ["delivered"], delivered: [],
};
```

**Imports:** `orders`, `products`, `getNextOrderId` from `../data.js`; `CreateOrderInput`, `Order`, `OrderItem` from `../types.js`; `ServiceError` from `./service-error.js`

---

## Files to Modify

### `src/routes/products.ts` (refactor)
Replace all business logic with service calls. Responsibilities after refactor:
- Parse `req.query` / `req.params` / `req.body` into typed values
- `typeof adjustment !== "number"` guard stays here (wire-format check, not a business rule)
- Call service functions; wrap throwing calls in try/catch
- Send HTTP responses

```typescript
import { Router } from "express";
import { ServiceError } from "../services/service-error.js";
import { listProducts, getProductById, adjustStock } from "../services/product-service.js";

const router = Router();

router.get("/products", (req, res) => {
  const { category, minPrice, maxPrice } = req.query;
  const filter: { category?: string; minPrice?: number; maxPrice?: number } = {};
  if (category && typeof category === "string") filter.category = category;
  if (minPrice && typeof minPrice === "string") { const v = parseFloat(minPrice); if (!isNaN(v)) filter.minPrice = v; }
  if (maxPrice && typeof maxPrice === "string") { const v = parseFloat(maxPrice); if (!isNaN(v)) filter.maxPrice = v; }
  res.json(listProducts(filter));
});

router.get("/products/:id", (req, res) => {
  const id = parseInt(req.params.id, 10);
  try { res.json(getProductById(id)); }
  catch (err) { if (err instanceof ServiceError) res.status(err.status).json({ error: err.message }); else throw err; }
});

router.patch("/products/:id/stock", (req, res) => {
  const id = parseInt(req.params.id, 10);
  const { adjustment } = req.body as { adjustment: unknown };
  if (typeof adjustment !== "number") { res.status(400).json({ error: "adjustment must be a number" }); return; }
  try { res.json(adjustStock(id, adjustment)); }
  catch (err) { if (err instanceof ServiceError) res.status(err.status).json({ error: err.message }); else throw err; }
});

export { router as productRouter };
```

### `src/routes/orders.ts` (refactor)
Same pattern — thin HTTP adapter delegating to service:

```typescript
import { Router } from "express";
import { ServiceError } from "../services/service-error.js";
import { listOrders, getOrderById, createOrder, updateOrderStatus } from "../services/order-service.js";
import type { CreateOrderInput } from "../types.js";

const router = Router();

router.get("/orders", (req, res) => {
  const { userId, status } = req.query;
  const filter: { userId?: number; status?: string } = {};
  if (userId && typeof userId === "string") { const v = parseInt(userId, 10); if (!isNaN(v)) filter.userId = v; }
  if (status && typeof status === "string") filter.status = status;
  res.json(listOrders(filter));
});

router.get("/orders/:id", (req, res) => {
  const id = parseInt(req.params.id, 10);
  try { res.json(getOrderById(id)); }
  catch (err) { if (err instanceof ServiceError) res.status(err.status).json({ error: err.message }); else throw err; }
});

router.post("/orders", (req, res) => {
  const input = req.body as CreateOrderInput;
  try { res.status(201).json(createOrder(input)); }
  catch (err) { if (err instanceof ServiceError) res.status(err.status).json({ error: err.message }); else throw err; }
});

router.patch("/orders/:id/status", (req, res) => {
  const id = parseInt(req.params.id, 10);
  const { status } = req.body as { status: string };
  try { res.json(updateOrderStatus(id, status)); }
  catch (err) { if (err instanceof ServiceError) res.status(err.status).json({ error: err.message }); else throw err; }
});

export { router as orderRouter };
```

---

## Files NOT Modified
- `src/types.ts` — existing types are reused as-is
- `src/data.ts` — data store and `getNextOrderId()` are reused as-is
- `src/app.ts` — no changes needed
- `tests/products.test.ts`, `tests/orders.test.ts` — integration tests must pass unchanged

---

## Error Propagation Strategy
`ServiceError(message, status)` is thrown by service functions for all business-rule
failures. Route handlers catch it and call `res.status(err.status).json({ error: err.message })`.
Any non-`ServiceError` is re-thrown, letting Express's default handler deal with
unexpected errors. This keeps route handlers free of business-rule knowledge while
preserving exact HTTP status codes and error messages the tests expect.

---

## Implementation Order
1. Create `src/services/service-error.ts`
2. Create `src/services/product-service.ts`
3. Create `src/services/order-service.ts`
4. Rewrite `src/routes/products.ts`
5. Rewrite `src/routes/orders.ts`
6. Run `vitest run` — all tests must pass

## Verification
```bash
npx vitest run
```
All 11 tests across `tests/products.test.ts` and `tests/orders.test.ts` must pass.

